                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72113/1141: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-22T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 11, 8 p.m. and November 3, 4 p.m. Department cannot understand why
                    the addresserdo [<hi rend="italic">acuerdo</hi>] referred to in your telegrams
                    of November 11, 8 p.m., and November <pb facs="0386" n="301" xml:id="pg_301"/>
                    3, 4 p.m., has not been published. The Department thinks that it should be
                    published at the earliest moment and desires to be informed of the date when it
                    will be published. You are instructed to bring this matter again to the
                    attention of the Guatemalan Government and to impress upon it the importance
                    with which the Department regards this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
